The Commonwealth Games Federation advises that a second Nigerian athlete, hurdler Samuel Okon, has tested positive for a banned substance Methylhexaneamine at the 2010 Commonwealth Games in Delhi, India. (ABC News Australia)Nigerian athlete Oludamola Osayomi, the winner of the 100 metres sprint at the 2010 Commonwealth Games in Delhi, India, tests positive for the banned stimulant Methylhexanamine. (AFP via Yahoo! News Australia), (ABC News Australia), ( Sky Sports)